obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (25824)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25824&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the National Institute of Fashion`
  line `Technology Act, 2006.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date ^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 1st April, 2007, vide notification No. S.O. 2159(E), dated 27th December, 2006, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (25825)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25825&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "appointed day" means the date of establishment of the National Institute of Fashion`
  line `Technology under sub-section (1) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) "Board" means the Board of Governors of the Institute constituted under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `c) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the Institute nominated under clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 3;`
  line
  line `d) "Director-General" means the Director-General of the Institute appointed under section 15;`
  line
  line `(e) "fashion" includes a popular trend or a lifestyle, specially in styles of dress and ornament or`
  line `manners of behaviour or the business of creating, promoting or studying styles in vogue or the`
  line `designing, production and marketing of new styles of goods such as, clothing, accessories, craft and`
  line `cosmetics; and the words "fashion technology" with their grammatical variations and cognate`
  line `expressions, shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(f) "Fund" means the Fund of the Institute to be maintained under section 19;`
  line
  line `(g) "Institute" means the National Institute of Fashion Technology established under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(h) "Institute Campus" means an Institute Campus located at New Delhi, Gandhinagar, Chennai,`
  line `Mumbai, Hyderabad, Bangalore, Kolkata or any other place in India or abroad as may be decided by`
  line `the Board of Governors;`
  line
  line `(i) "Senate" means the Senate of the Institute referred to in section 12;`
  line
  line `(j) "Society" means the National Institute of Fashion Technology, New Delhi registered as a`
  line `society under the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860);`
  line
  line `(k) "Statutes and Ordinances" mean respectively the Statutes and the Ordinances of the Institute`
  line `made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (25826)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment of the Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25826&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central Government may,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette appoint, the National Institute of Fashion Technology shall be`
  line `established as a body corporate by the name aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(2) The Institute shall have perpetual succession and a common seal with power, subject to the`
  line `provisions of this Act, to acquire, hold and dispose of property and to contract, and shall, by that name,`
  line `sue or be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The Institute shall consist of the Board of Governors having the following persons, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson, who shall be an eminent academician, scientist or technologist or professional,`
  line `to be nominated by the Visitor;`
  line
  line `(b) three Members of Parliament, two from Lok Sabha to be nominated by the Speaker of Lok`
  line `Sabha and one from Rajya Sabha to be nominated by the Chairman of Rajya Sabha;`
  line
  line `(c) the Director-General of the Institute, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) the Financial Adviser of the Ministry or Department in the Government of India dealing with`
  line `the National Institute of Fashion Technology, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) the Joint Secretary, in the Ministry or Department in the Government of India dealing with the`
  line `National Institute of Fashion Technology, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(f) the representative of the Ministry or Department in the Government of India dealing with`
  line `higher education to be nominated by the Secretary of that Ministry or Department, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(g) five persons to be nominated by the Central Government, representing the States in which the`
  line `campus of the Institute is located, from amongst persons who are academicians or industrialists of`
  line `repute engaged in area of fashion technology; and`
  line
  line `(h) two eminent experts in fashion technology, one of whom shall be an educationist, to be`
  line `nominated by the Visitor on the recommendations of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) The term of office of the Chairperson and other members of the Board other than ex officio`
  line `members thereof shall be three years and they shall be entitled for such allowances as may be determined`
  line `by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) The term of office of members of the Board nominated to fill a casual vacancy shall continue for`
  line `the remainder of the term of the member in whose place he has been nominated.`
  line
  line `(6) The Board shall meet at least four times in a year at such place and time and observe such rules of`
  line `procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings as may be determined by the Board.`
  line
  line `(7) It is hereby declared that the office of member of the Board of Governors shall not disqualify its`
  line `holder for being chosen as, or for being, a member of either House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (25827)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Vesting of properties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25827&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day, subject to the other provisions of this Act,`
  line `all properties which had vested in the Society, immediately before the commencement of this Act, shall`
  line `on and from such commencement, vest in the Institute.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (25828)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Effect of incorporation of Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25828&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `On and from the appointed day--`
  line
  line `(a) any reference to the Society in any contract or other instrument shall be deemed as a reference`
  line `to the Institute;`
  line
  line `(b) all the rights and liabilities of the Society shall be transferred to, and be the rights and`
  line `liabilities of, the Institute; and`
  line
  line `(c) every person employed by the Society, immediately before the appointed day, shall hold`
  line `office or service in the Institute by the same tenure, at the same remuneration and upon the same`
  line `terms and conditions and with the same rights and privileges as to pension, leave, gratuity, provident`
  line `fund and other matters as he would have held the same, if this Act had not been passed, and shall`
  line `continue to be so, unless and until his employment is terminated or until such tenure, remuneration,`
  line `terms and conditions are duly altered by the Statutes:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the alteration so made is not acceptable to such employee, his employment may`
  line `be terminated by the Institute in accordance with the terms of the contract with the employee or, if no`
  line `provision is made therein in this behalf, on payment to him by the Institute of compensation`
  line `equivalent to three months remuneration in the case of permanent employee and one month's`
  line `remuneration in the case of other employee.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (25829)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Functions of Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25829&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The functions of the Institute shall be--`
  line
  line `(i) to nurture and promote quality and excellence in education and research in area of fashion`
  line technology;
  line
  line `(ii) to lay down courses leading to graduate and post-graduate degrees, doctoral and post-doctoral`
  line `courses and research in area of fashion technology;`
  line
  line `(iii) to hold examinations and grant degrees in area of fashion technology;`
  line
  line `(iv) to confer honorary degrees, awards or other distinctions in area of fashion technology;`
  line
  line `(v) to cooperate with educational or other institutions in any part of the world having objects`
  line `wholly or partly similar to those of the Institute by exchange of faculty members and scholars and`
  line `generally in such manner as may be conducive to their common objective;`
  line
  line `(vi) to conduct courses for teachers, fashion technologists and other professionals;`
  line
  line `(vii) to undertake research and studies in area of fashion technology and application thereof,`
  line `particularly concerning the integration of locally produced materials, the requirements of mass`
  line `production, improved quality and design and international marketing;`
  line
  line `(viii) to collect and maintain literature and materials available in area of fashion technology so as`
  line `to develop a modern information centre within the country;`
  line
  line `(ix) to create a central faculty of fashion technology resource and analysis for use by the`
  line researchers;
  line
  line `(x) to have a centre to experiment and innovate and to train persons in the area of fashion`
  line technology;
  line
  line `(xi) to develop an international centre for creation and transmission of information in the area of`
  line `fashion technology, with focus on educational, professional and industrial commitments;`
  line
  line `(xii) to develop a multi-disciplinary approach in carrying out research and training in area of`
  line `fashion technology so that the larger interests of the profession, academia and fashion industry are`
  line `better served;`
  line
  line `(xiii) to organise national or international symposia, seminars, conferences and exhibitions in`
  line `selected area of fashion technology, from time to time;`
  line
  line `(xiv) to arrange courses catering to the special needs of the developing countries;`
  line
  line `(xv) to act as a nucleus for interaction between academia and industry by encouraging exchange`
  line `of fashion technologists and other technical staff between the Institute and the industry and by`
  line `undertaking sponsored and funded research as well as consultancy projects by the Institute;`
  line
  line `(xvi) to provide technical assistance to artisans, craftsmen, manufacturers, designers and exporters`
  line `of fashion products; and`
  line
  line `(xvii) to carry out any other activity in the area of fashion technology not specifically listed`
  line above.
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (25830)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Powers of Board.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25830&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Board, under overall control of`
  line `the Central Government, shall be responsible for the general superintendence, direction and control of the`
  line `affairs of the Institute and shall exercise all the powers not otherwise provided for by this Act, the Statutes`
  line `and the Ordinances, and shall have the power to review the acts of the Senate.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Board shall--`
  line
  line `(a) take decisions on questions of policy relating to the administration and working of the`
  line Institute;
  line
  line `(b) take decisions on the establishment of new campuses of the Institute at any location in India`
  line `or abroad;`
  line
  line `(c) fix, demand and receive fees and other charges;`
  line
  line `(d) establish, maintain and manage halls and hostels for the residence of the students;`
  line
  line `(e) supervise and control the residence and regulate the discipline of students of the Institute and`
  line `to make arrangements for promoting their health, general welfare and cultural and corporate life;`
  line
  line `(f) institute academic and other posts and to make appointments thereto (except in the case of the`
  line `Director-General);`
  line
  line `(g) frame Statutes and Ordinances and to alter, modify or rescind the same;`
  line
  line `(h) institute and award fellowships, scholarships, prizes and medals;`
  line
  line `(i) consider and pass resolutions on the annual report, the annual accounts and the budget`
  line `estimates of the Institute for the next financial year as it thinks fit together with a statement of its`
  line `development plans;`
  line
  line `(j) receive gifts, grants, donations or benefactions from the Government and to receive bequests,`
  line `donations and transfers of movable or immovable properties from the testators, donors or transferors,`
  line `as the case may be; and`
  line
  line `(k) do all such things as may be necessary, incidental or conducive to the attainment of all or any`
  line `of the aforesaid powers.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall have the power to appoint such committees, as it considers necessary for the`
  line `exercise of its powers and the performance of its duties under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2) of section 3, the Board shall not dispose of`
  line `in any manner any immovable property without the prior approval of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may appoint one or more persons to review the work and progress of the`
  line `Institute and to hold inquiries into the affairs thereof and to report thereon in such manner as the Central`
  line `Government may direct.`
  line
  line `(6) Upon receipt of any such report, the Central Government may take such action and issue such`
  line `directions as it considers necessary in respect of any of the matters dealt with in the report and the`
  line `Institute shall be bound to comply with such directions.`
  line
  line `(7) The Visitor shall have the power to remove the Chairperson or other members of the Board`
  line `nominated by him, on the recommendations of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(8) The Central Government shall have the power to remove other members, if it considers it`
  line `appropriate to do so.`
  line
  line `(9) No Chairperson or member shall be removed under sub-section (7) or sub-section (8) unless he`
  line `has been given a reasonable opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (25831)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Institute be open to all races, creeds and classes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25831&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Institute shall be open to persons of`
  line `either sex and of whatever race, creed, caste or class, and no test or condition shall be imposed as to`
  line `religious belief or profession in admitting or appointing members, students, teachers or workers or in any`
  line `other connection whatsoever.`
  line
  line `(2) No bequest, donation or transfer of any property shall be accepted by the Institute, which in the`
  line `opinion of the Board involves conditions or obligations opposed to the spirit and object of this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (25832)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Teaching at Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25832&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `All teaching at the campuses of the Institute shall be conducted by or in`
  line `the name of the Institute in accordance with the Statutes and the Ordinances made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (25833)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title Visitor.
  content `The President of India shall be the Visitor of the Institute.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25833&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (25834)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Authorities of Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25834&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `The following shall be the authorities of the Institute, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a Board of Governors;`
  line
  line `(b) a Senate; and`
  line
  line `(c) such other authorities as may be declared by the Statutes to be the authorities of the Institute.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (25835)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title Senate.
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25835&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The Senate of the Institute shall consist of the following persons, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the Director-General, ex officio who shall be the Chairperson of the Senate;`
  line
  line `(b) all Institute Campus Directors and Senior Professors;`
  line
  line `(c) three persons, not being employees of the Institute, to be nominated by the Chairperson in`
  line `consultation with the Director-General, from amongst educationists of repute, one each from the`
  line `fields of science, engineering and humanities and one of them shall be either from the Scheduled`
  line `Castes or the Scheduled Tribes;`
  line
  line `(d) one alumnus of the Institute to be nominated by the Chairperson in consultation with the`
  line `Director-General by rotation; and`
  line
  line `(e) such other members of the staff as may be laid down in the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (25836)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Functions of Senate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25836&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes and the Ordinances, the`
  line `Senate of the Institute shall have the control and general regulation, and be responsible for the`
  line `maintenance of standards of instruction, education and examination in the Institute and shall exercise such`
  line `other powers and perform such other duties as may be conferred or imposed upon it by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (25837)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Functions, powers and duties of Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25837&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson shall ordinarily preside at`
  line `the meetings of the Board and at the Convocations of the Institute.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson shall exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be`
  line `assigned to him by this Act or the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (25838)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title Director-General.
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25838&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Director-General of the Institute shall be appointed by the Board`
  line `with the prior approval of the Central Government for a tenure of three years.`
  line
  line `(2) The Director-General shall be the principal executive officer of the Institute and shall be`
  line `responsible for the proper administration of the Institute and for imparting of instruction and maintenance`
  line `of discipline therein.`
  line
  line `(3) The Director-General shall submit annual reports and accounts to the Board.`
  line
  line `(4) The Director-General shall exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be`
  line `assigned to him by this Act, Statutes and Ordinances.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government shall have the power to remove the Director-General before the tenure of`
  line `three years, if it considers it appropriate to do so.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (25839)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title Registrar.
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25839&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Registrar of the Institute shall be appointed on such terms and conditions as`
  line `may be laid down by the Statutes and shall be the custodian of records, the common seal, the funds of the`
  line `Institute and such other property of the Institute as the Board shall commit to his charge.`
  line
  line `(2) The Registrar shall act as the Secretary of the Board, the Senate and such committees as may be`
  line `prescribed by the Statutes.`
  line
  line `(3) The Registrar shall be responsible to the Director-General for the proper discharge of his`
  line functions.
  line
  line `(4) The Registrar shall exercise such other powers and perform such other duties as may be assigned`
  line `to him by this Act or the Statutes or by the Director-General.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (25840)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Powers and duties of other authorities and officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25840&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The powers and duties of authorities and`
  line `officers, other than those hereinbefore mentioned, shall be determined by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (25841)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Grants by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25841&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of enabling the Institute to discharge its`
  line `functions efficiently under this Act, the Central Government may, after due appropriation made by`
  line `Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Institute in each financial year such sums of money and in`
  line `such manner as it may think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (25842)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Fund by Institute.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25842&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Institute shall maintain a Fund to which shall be credited--`
  line
  line `(a) all moneys provided by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) all fees and other charges received by the Institute;`
  line
  line `(c) all moneys received by the Institute by way of grants, gifts, donations, benefactions, bequests`
  line `or transfers; and`
  line
  line `(d) all moneys received by the Institute in any other manner or from any other source.`
  line
  line `(2) All moneys credited to the Fund shall be deposited in such banks or invested in such manner as`
  line `the Institute may, with the approval of the Central Government, decide.`
  line
  line `(3) The fund shall be applied towards meeting the expenses of the Institute including expenses`
  line `incurred in the exercise of its powers and discharge of its duties under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (25843)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Setting up of endowment fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25843&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 19, the Central`
  line `Government may direct the Institute to--`
  line
  line `(a) set up an endowment fund and any other fund for specified purpose; and`
  line
  line `(b) transfer money from its Fund to endowment fund or any other fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (25844)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25844&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Institute shall maintain proper accounts and other relevant records`
  line `and prepare an annual statement of accounts, including the balance-sheet, in such form as may be`
  line `specified, in accordance with such general directions as may be issued by the Central Government in`
  line `consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Institute shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and`
  line `any expenditure incurred by him in connection with such audit shall be payable by the Institute to the`
  line `Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India and any person appointed by him in connection`
  line `with the audit of the accounts of the Institute shall have the same rights, privileges and authority in`
  line `connection with such audit as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India, generally has in connection`
  line `with the audit of the Government accounts, and, in particular, shall have the right to demand the`
  line `production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect any of`
  line `the offices of the Institute.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Institute as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf, together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (25845)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Pension and provident fund.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25845&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Institute shall constitute, for the benefit of its employees,`
  line `including the Director-General, in such manner and subject to such conditions as may be prescribed by`
  line `the Statutes, such pension, insurance and provident funds as it may consider necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any such provident fund has been so constituted, the Central Government may declare that`
  line `the provisions of the Provident Funds Act, 1925 (19 of 1925) shall apply to such fund as if it were a`
  line `Government Provident Fund.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (25846)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title Appointment.
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25846&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `All appointments of the staff of the Institute, except that of the DirectorGeneral,`
  line `shall be made in accordance with the procedure laid down in the Statutes by--`
  line
  line `(a) the Board, if the appointment is made on the academic staff in the post of Assistant Professor`
  line `or above or if the appointment is made on the non-academic staff in any cadre, the maximum of the`
  line `pay-scale for which is the same or higher than that of Assistant Professor; and`
  line
  line `(b) the Director-General, in any other case.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (25847)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title Statutes.
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25847&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Statutes may provide for all or any of the`
  line `following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the formation of departments of teaching;`
  line
  line `(b) the institution of fellowships, scholarships, exhibitions, medals and prizes;`
  line
  line `(c) the classification, the method of appointment and the determination of the terms and`
  line `conditions of service of officers, teachers and other staff of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(d) the reservation of posts for the Scheduled Castes, the Scheduled Tribes and other backward`
  line `categories of persons as may be determined by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(e) the constitution of pension, insurance and provident funds for the benefit of the officers,`
  line `teachers and other staff of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(f) the constitution, powers and duties of the authorities of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(g) the establishment and maintenance of halls and hostels;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner of filling up of vacancies among members of the Board;`
  line
  line `(i) the authentication of the orders and decisions of the Board;`
  line
  line `(j) the meetings of the Senate, the quorum at such meetings and the procedure to be followed in`
  line `the conduct of their business; and`
  line
  line `(k) any other matter which by this Act is to be or may be prescribed by the Statutes.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (25848)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Statutes how made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25848&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The first Statutes of the Institute shall be framed by the Board with the`
  line `previous approval of the Visitor and a copy of the same shall be laid as soon as may be before each House`
  line `of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may, from time to time, make new or additional Statutes or may amend or repeal the`
  line `Statutes in the manner hereafter in this section provided.`
  line
  line `(3) Every new Statute or addition to the Statute or any amendment or repeal of a Statute shall require`
  line `the previous approval of the Visitor who may assent thereto or withhold assent or remit it to the Board for`
  line consideration.
  line
  line `(4) A new Statute or a Statute amending or repealing an existing Statute shall have no validity unless`
  line `it has been assented to by the Visitor.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (25849)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title Ordinances.
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25849&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act and the Statutes, the Ordinances of the`
  line `Institute may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the admission of the students to the Institute;`
  line
  line `(b) the reservation for the Scheduled Castes, the Scheduled Tribes and other backward categories`
  line `of persons;`
  line
  line `(c) the courses of study to be laid down for all degrees, diplomas and certificates of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(d) the conditions under which students shall be admitted to the degree, diploma and certificate`
  line `courses and to the examinations of the Institute and award of degrees, diplomas and certificates;`
  line
  line `(e) the conditions for award of fellowships, scholarships, exhibitions, medals and prizes;`
  line
  line `(f) the conditions and mode of appointment and duties of examining body, examiners and`
  line moderators;
  line
  line `(g) the conduct of examinations;`
  line
  line `(h) the maintenance of discipline among the students of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(i) the fees to be charged for courses of study in the Institute and for admission to the`
  line `examinations of degrees, diplomas and certificates of the Institute;`
  line
  line `(j) the conditions of residence of students of the Institute and the levying of the fees for residence`
  line `in the halls and hostels and other charges; and`
  line
  line `(k) any other matter which by this Act or the Statutes is to be or may be provided for by the`
  line Ordinances.
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (25850)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Ordinances how made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25850&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) Save as otherwise provided in this section, Ordinances shall be`
  line `made by the Senate.`
  line
  line `(2) All Ordinances made by the Senate shall have effect from such date as it may direct, but every`
  line `Ordinance so made shall be submitted, as soon as may be, to the Board and shall be considered by the`
  line `Board at its next succeeding meeting.`
  line
  line `(3) The Board shall have power by resolution to modify or cancel any such Ordinance and such`
  line `Ordinance shall from the date of such resolution stand modified accordingly or cancelled, as the case may`
  line be.
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (25851)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Tribunal of Arbitration`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=25851&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any dispute arising out of a contract between the Institute and any`
  line `of its employees shall, at the request of the employee concerned or at the instance of the Institute, be`
  line `referred to a Tribunal of Arbitration consisting of one member appointed by the Institute, one member`
  line `nominated by the employee and an umpire appointed by the Visitor.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Tribunal of Arbitration shall be final and shall not be questioned in any court.`
  line
  line `(3) No suit or proceeding shall lie in any court in respect of any matter which is required by`
  line `sub-section (1) to be referred to the Tribunal of Arbitration.`
  line
  line `(4) The Tribunal of Arbitration shall have power to regulate its own procedure.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in any law for the time being in force relating to arbitration shall apply to arbitration`
  line `under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (27695)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Acts and proceedings not to be invalidated by vacancies, etc`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=27695&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `No act of the Institute or Board`
  line `or Senate or any other body set up under this Act or the Statutes, shall be invalid merely by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or defect in the constitution thereof; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the election, nomination or appointment of a person acting as a member thereof;`
  line or
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in its procedure not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (27696)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Sponsored schemes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=27696&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, whenever the Institute`
  line `receives funds from any Government, the University Grants Commission or any other agency including`
  line `industry sponsoring a research scheme or a consultancy assignment or a teaching programme or a chaired`
  line `professorship or a scholarship, etc., to be executed or endowed at the Institute:--`
  line
  line `(a) the amount received shall be kept by the Institute separately from the Fund of the Institute and`
  line `utilised only for the purpose of the scheme; and`
  line
  line `(b) the staff required to execute the same shall be recruited in accordance with the terms and`
  line `conditions stipulated by the sponsoring organisations:`
  line
  line `Provided that any money remaining unutilised shall be transferred to the endowment fund created`
  line `under section 20 of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (27697)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Power of Institute to grant degrees, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=27697&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `The Institute shall have the power to grant degrees,`
  line `diplomas, certificates and other academic distinctions under this Act, which shall be equivalent to such`
  line `corresponding degrees, diplomas, certificates and other academic distinctions granted by any University`
  line `or Institute established or incorporated under any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (27698)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Powers to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=27698&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provision or`
  line `give such direction not inconsistent with the purposes of this Act, as appears to it to be necessary or`
  line `expedient for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of two years from the appointed day.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (27699)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Transitional provisions`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=27699&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act--`
  line
  line `(a) the Board of Governors of the Society functioning as such immediately before the`
  line `commencement of this Act shall continue to so function until a new Board is constituted for the`
  line `Institute under this Act, but on the constitution of a new Board under this Act the members of the`
  line `Board holding office before such constitution shall cease to hold office; and`
  line
  line `(b) until the first Statutes and the Ordinances are made under this Act, the rules and regulations,`
  line `instructions and guidelines of the Society as in force, immediately before the commencement of this`
  line `Act, shall continue to apply to the Institute in so far as they are not inconsistent with the provisions of`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (27700)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Statutes and Ordinances to be published in the Official Gazette and to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274&sectionId=27700&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_20_25_000010_200628_1517807326274
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Statute or Ordinance made under this Act shall be published in the Official`
  line Gazette.
  line
  line `(2) Every Statute or Ordinance made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made,`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the Statute or Ordinance or both Houses agree that the Statute or Ordinance should not be`
  line `made, the Statute or Ordinance shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect,`
  line `as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to`
  line `the validity of anything previously done under that Statute or Ordinance.`
  line
  line `(3) The power to make Statutes or Ordinances shall include the power to give retrospective effect`
  line `from a date not earlier than the date of commencement of this Act to Statutes or Ordinances or any of`
  line `them but no retrospective effect shall be given to any Statute or Ordinance so as to prejudicially affect the`
  line `interests of any person to whom such Statutes or Ordinances may be applicable.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
